<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-09"><hi rend="italic">April 9,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 216.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that I have
                            just telegraphed you in cipher as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>, <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1898.</hi></p>
                                <p rend="flushleft">Assistant Secretary <hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                                <p>No change in situation. Spanish propositions of March 31 have not
                                    been modified. It is still possible that armistice may be
                                    declared. I will keep you fully advised.</p>
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford.</hi></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>There are rumors this morning of a possible ministerial crisis, but I can
                            not verify them at this moment.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully, yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>